{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e72398df-6534-4108-b6ea-26437f279307","content":"Here's what I've set up and what you need to do:\n\n## GitHub Actions Workflow (`.github/workflows/publish.yml`)\n\nCreated a workflow that triggers on version tags (`v*`), packs your library, and pushes to NuGet **without an API key** — using OIDC via the `id-token: write` permission.\n\n## You still need to configure NuGet.org\n\nOn [nuget.org](https://www.nuget.org), register your package's trusted publisher:\n\n1. Go to your package (or account) → **Manage** → **Trusted Publishers**\n2. Add a new **GitHub Actions** publisher:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository name:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** *(leave blank unless you add a GitHub environment)*\n\n## To publish\n\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\nThe workflow will authenticate via OIDC automatically — no `NUGET_API_KEY` secret needed. Make sure your `.csproj` has `<PackageId>`, `<Version>`, and other required package metadata.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1a80eabb-ed22-4630-aa3e-f38d14a1cebe","outputTokens":283,"requestId":"1018:14859A:AAB8D23:B971B5C:69FD344D"},"id":"1309b202-f13a-4ec4-a1fc-83c1cb2138c6","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:54:45.228Z","parentId":"85ce3d3b-0009-4364-b104-93abb2476ec4"}
